# Worker Environment Configuration

# Local Development
# No secrets needed for local development - uses default 'dev-local-key'

# Remote Environments
# For dev, staging, and production, set secrets using wrangler:

# Development Environment (bench-api-dev.zephyr-cloud.io)
# wrangler secret put API_SECRET_KEY --env dev
# Example: a secure random string for authentication

# Staging Environment (bench-api-stg.zephyr-cloud.io)
# wrangler secret put API_SECRET_KEY --env staging
# Example: a different secure random string

# Production Environment (bench-api.zephyr-cloud.io)
# wrangler secret put API_SECRET_KEY --env production
# Example: a strong production secret

# Additional secrets can be added as needed:
# wrangler secret put SOME_OTHER_SECRET --env production
